Pattern topology from the drawing

Model constraints

1. Every node must have exactly 4 connections to other nodes.

2. The graph girth must be at least 6.
That means there are no closed loops anywhere in the graph with fewer than 6
connections.

3. Taking any node as the current root, the graph should expose 12 distinct
loops of length 6 from that root.
Equivalently, around each chosen root there must be 12 six-connection cycles in
the graph.

Expansion model

The program now treats the drawn pattern as a seed neighborhood and then grows
the graph by root shifts.

1. Build the exact image pattern once around the initial root.

2. When the root shifts onto an already discovered node, traverse its current
neighbors and reuse the existing part of the local two-level neighborhood.

3. If the shifted root is missing first-level or second-level nodes, create the
missing nodes off the current frontier.

4. Count the already existing 6-connection loops visible from that shifted root.

5. Add only the missing split nodes between second-level nodes from different
branches until the shifted root has 12 loops of length 6, while preserving the
minimum cycle length of 6 and never exceeding degree 4 on any node.

6. Newly created frontier nodes may be temporarily under-connected until a later
shift expands around them. The completion pass is what brings a chosen local
neighborhood up to the model constraints.

Typed expansion model

The current implementation no longer assumes that every shifted root can be
completed with the same local rule.

It now distinguishes several node roles:

- center: the 4-way hub type used by the original seed root
- branch: a node with one center-side neighbor and three leaf-side neighbors
- leaf: a node between a branch-side neighbor, split-side neighbors, and outward
  frontier structure
- split: a node that sits on a loop bridge between two leaf-side regions
- frontier: newly created outward nodes that are not yet fully specialized

Completion is role-specific:

- center roots use the original image seed pattern and local pairing planner
- branch roots use a separate neighborhood shape and branch-specific loop filler
- leaf, split, and frontier nodes are still incomplete in the current model and
  remain the active refinement area for deeper expansion

